Π. Modo signifying ‘just now’ or ‘this moment! Modus, as stated above, signifies generally ‘a measure,¹ specially it denotes ‘a measure of time,’ ‘an unit of time‚' and is employed with reference to the unit of time immediately preceding an event; or, during which an event is taking place ; or, immediately following an event. So in English we say, 1. he was here just now, this moment, this instant; 2. he is here just now (this moment, this instant); 3. he will be here just now, this moment, this instant.
